article.headline: Lafayette 76, Army 40
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Winston Davis scored 17 points on the strength of 5 of 7 shooting from beyond the 3-point line to lead Lafayette to a 76-40 win over Army on Wednesday. Lafayette (11-4, 2-0 Patriot League) shot 13 of 26 from beyond the arc to just 3 of 18 for Army (3-11, 0-2). Mike Farrell added 11 points -- going 5 for 5 from the floor -- for the Leopards and Justin DeBerry and Marcus Harley added 10 points each in the win. Josh Wilson scored 19 points to lead Army and Sean O'Keefe chipped in 10. Lafayette held a 34-25 advantage at halftime but used a 30-4 run at the start of the second half to blow the game open. Army made just 4 of 21 second-half attempts. Lafayette also forced 23 turnovers. The 40 points allowed by Lafayette were the fewest since a 47-40 win over Colgate in 1985.
